main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified objects reported over El Centro, California on 13 May 1952.
interesting points: Five flying saucers as large as B-36s were reported hovering and moving rapidly, A pilot at El Centro Naval Air Station reported seeing a shooting star around the same time, The Imperial Police Department noted a large object with lights that was observed for several minutes, Radar crews detected unusual activity in the area, There were conflicting reports about whether the objects were meteorological phenomena or unidentified craft.
witness description: Deputy Sheriffs, pilots, and control tower operators
